            "level": 15,
            "entries": [
                "When you use your Indomitable feature, each creature of your choice within a 10-foot emanation originating from you must succeed on a Strength saving throw against your Arcane Shot DC or be pushed 15 feet away from you."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 18: Arcane Evasion",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Arcane Archer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 18,
            "entries": [
                "When a creature misses you with an attack, you can take a reaction to teleport up to 15 feet to an unoccupied space you can see. You can then make a ranged attack roll against the attacker as part of the same reaction."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Elegant Courtier",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Samurai",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You gain proficiency in one of the following skills of your choice: {@skill History}, {@skill Insight}, {@skill Performance}, or {@skill Persuasion}. In addition, whenever you make a Charisma check using a skill you are proficient in, you gain a bonus equal to your Wisdom modifier."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Fighting Spirit",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Samurai",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "When you take the {@action Attack} Action, you can give yourself advantage on every attack you make in this turn and gain a number of temporary hit points equal to your Fighter level. You can use this feature once, regaining expended uses when you finish a Long rest."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 7: Focussed Fighter",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Samurai",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 7,
            "entries": [
                "You gain proficiency in Wisdom saving throws. If you already have this proficiency, you instead gain proficiency in Intelligence or Charisma saving throws (your choice)."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 10: Rapid Strike",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Samurai",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 10,
            "entries": [
                "Once every turn, as part of the {@action Attack} Action, when you make an attack with advantage, you can forgo the advantage to make an additional weapon attack as part of the same action."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 15: Tireless Spirit",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Samurai",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 15,
            "entries": [
                "When you roll initiative you regain expended uses of Fighting Spirit until you have 2, if you have 1 or fewer."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 18: Strength Before Death",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Samurai",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 18,
            "entries": [
                "When you drop to 0 hit points, you can use your reaction to delay falling {@condition unconscious} and immediately take an extra turn. Taking damage causes death saves failure and can kill you. At the end of this extra turn, you fall {@condition unconscious}."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Kensei Weapon",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Kensei",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Choose one melee and one ranged weapon to be your kensei weapons. They can be any weapon that lacks the heavy and special properties, or a Longbow. You are proficient in them, can use their properties with your martial arts features, and they count as monk weapons."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Path of the Kensei",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Kensei",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You gain proficiency in calligrapher's supplies or painter's supplies. In addition, once every turn, you can gain one of the following benefits:",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Agile Parry",
                            "entries": [
                                "While you're holding a melee kensei weapon and are not {@condition incapacitated}, you gain a +2 bonus to AC."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Kensei's Shot",
                            "entries": [
                                "When you hit with a ranged kensei weapon as part of the {@action Attack} Action, you can deal extra damage equal to one roll of your Martial Arts die."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: One with the Blade",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Kensei",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "You extend your power into your kensei weapons, granting you the following benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Kensei Blow",
                            "entries": [
                                "You can make an attack with a kensei weapon as a Bonus Action."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Deft Strike",
                            "entries": [
                                "Once every turn, when you hit a target with a kensei weapon, you can spend 1 Focus Point to deal extra damage equal to a roll of your Martial Arts die."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 11: Sharpen the Blade",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Kensei",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 11,
            "entries": [
                "At the start of your turn, you can expend up to 3 Focus Points to empower one kensei weapon you touch. That weapon gains a bonus to attack and damage rolls equal the number of discipline points spent until the end of your turn."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 17: Kensei Master",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Kensei",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 17,
            "entries": [
                "At the peak of your fighting prowess, you gain the following benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Kensei Flurry",
                            "entries": [
                                "You can expend 1 Focus Point to make two attacks with a Kensei Weapon as a Bonus Action."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Unerring Accuracy",
                            "entries": [
                                "Your mastery of weapons grants you extraordinary accuracy. If you miss with an attack roll using a monk weapon on your turn, you can reroll it. You can use this feature only once on each of your turns."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Radiant Awakening",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Sun",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "At the start of your turn, you can spend 1 discipline point to wreathe yourself in radiant energy for 10 minutes. For the duration you gain the following benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        "Once every turn, when you hit with an attack, you can deal extra radiant damage equal to one roll of your Martial Arts die.",
                        "Once every turn, you can replace an Unarmed Strike attack to make a ranged attack using Dexterity against a creature within 60 feet of you. If the attack hits, it deals radiant damage equal to one roll of your Martial Arts die."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Searing Arc Strike",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Sun",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "As a bonus action, you can spend 1 Focus Point to emit a 15-foot cone of light from your hand. Each creature in the area must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save it takes radiant damage equal to two rolls of your Martial Arts die, or half as much on a successful one."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 11: Searing Sunburst",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Sun",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 11,
            "entries": [
                "As a Magic Action, you hurl a bolt of light at a point you can see within 60 feet of you. Each creature in that 20-foot radius sphere centered on that point must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take {@damage 6d6} radiant damage, or half as much on a successful one."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 17: Sun Avatar",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Sun",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 17,
            "entries": [
                "You become an avatar of radiant energy. You gain immunity to radiant damage and once per turn when you hit with an attack that deals radiant damage, you can force the target to make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, the target is {@condition blinded} until the end of its next turn."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Benign Transposition",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Conjurer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "As a Bonus Action, you teleport up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space that you can see. Alternatively, you can choose a willing creature within 30 feet, you both teleport swapping places. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of one) and regain all expended uses when you finish a Long rest."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Conjuration Savant",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Conjurer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Choose two Wizard spells from the Conjuration school, each of which must be no higher than level 1 or 2, and add them to your spellbook for free.",
                "In addition, whenever you gain access to a new level of spell slots in this class, you can add one Wizard spell from the Conjuration school to your spellbook for free. The chosen spell must be of a level for which you have spell slots."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Distant Transposition",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Conjurer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "The range of your Benign Transposition feature increases to 60 feet. Additionally, you now regain all expended uses of it when you finish a Short or Long rest."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Durable Summons",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Conjurer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "When you cast a Conjuration spell to summon or create a creature using a spell slot, that creature gains temporary hit points equal to twice your Wizard level when it first appears. While it has these temporary hit points, the creature has resistance to every damage type except Force, Necrotic, Psychic and Radiant."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 10: Focussed Conjuration",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Conjurer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 10,
            "entries": [
                "Taking damage can’t break your concentration on Conjuration spells."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 14: Splintered Summons",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Conjurer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 14,
            "entries": [
                "When you cast {@spell Summon Construct|xphb}, {@spell Summon Dragon|xphb}, {@spell Summon Elemental|xphb} or {@spell Summon Fey|xphb} using a spell slot, you can modify the spell to summon two creatures instead of one. Each creature uses the stat block and rules denoted by the spell and appears in a different unoccupied space of your choice within the spell’s range, but the summoned creatures’ hit points are halved. If you lose concentration on the spell, both creatures disappear."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Enchanting Voice",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Enchanter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Whenever you make a Charisma check, you gain a bonus to the check equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of +1). You also gain proficiency in one of these skills of your choice: {@skill Deception}, {@skill Intimidation} or {@skill Persuasion}."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Enchantment Savant",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Enchanter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Choose two Wizard spells from the Enchantment school, each of which must be no higher than level 1 or 2, and add them to your spellbook for free.",
                "In addition, whenever you gain access to a new level of spell slots in this class, you can add one Wizard spell from the Enchantment school to your spellbook for free. The chosen spell must be of a level for which you have spell slots."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Hypnotic Presence",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Enchanter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "As a Magic Action, choose one creature that you can see within 30 feet of yourself. If the target can see or hear you, it must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw against your spell save DC or have the {@condition charmed} condition for 1 minute or until it takes damage. While {@condition charmed} in this way, the target has the {@condition incapacitated} condition and a speed of 0. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of once) and regain all expended uses when you finish a Long rest."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Split Enchantment",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Enchanter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "When you use your Hypnotic Presence feature or cast an Enchantment spell that targets only one creature, you can target one additional creature with it. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of once) and regain all expended uses when you finish a Long rest."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 10: Instinctive Charm",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Enchanter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 10,
            "entries": [
                "When a creature within 30 feet of you that you can see hits deals damage to you, you can take a Reaction to force it to make a Wisdom saving throw against your spell save DC. On a failed save, the damage you take is reduced to 0 and another creature of your choice within 30 feet takes the same amount of damage. Once you use this Reaction, you can’t do so again until you finish a Long rest. You can restore your use of this feature by casting an Enchantment spell with a spell slot."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 14: Superior Enchantment",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Enchanter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 14,
            "entries": [
                "When you use your Hypnotic Presence feature or cast an Enchantment spell that causes the {@condition charmed} condition, you can ignore immunities to the {@condition charmed} condition. Once you use this feature, you cannot do so again until you finish a Long rest."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Necromancy Savant",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Necromancer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Choose two Wizard spells from the Necromancy school, each of which must be no higher than level 1 or 2, and add them to your spellbook for free.",
                "In addition, whenever you gain access to a new level of spell slots in this class, you can add one Wizard spell from the Necromancy school to your spellbook for free. The chosen spell must be of a level for which you have spell slots."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Necromancy Spellbook",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Necromancer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Your mastery of necromantic lore grants you extra abilities.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Necrotic Resistance",
                            "entries": [
                                "You gain resistance to Necrotic damage."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Grim Harvest",
                            "entries": [
                                "When you cast a Necromancy spell using a spell slot, you can choose an undead creature you can see within 60 feet of you and make it regain hit points equal to the level of the spell slot expended plus your Wizard level."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Undead Familiar",
                            "entries": [
                                "{@spell Find Familiar|xphb} is added to your spellbook. When you cast the spell, you can choose the Skeleton or Zombie forms in addition to the normal forms."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Undead Thralls",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Necromancer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "{@spell Summon Undead|xphb} is added to your spellbook and you always have it prepared. Whenever you cast the spell, the summoned creature gains the following benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Undead Fortitude",
                            "entries": [
                                "The creature’s hit point maximum and current hit points increase by a number equal to the level of the spell slot used plus your Intelligence modifier."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Withering Strike",
                            "entries": [
                                "Whenever the creature hits with an attack roll, it deals extra damage equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of one)."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 10: Harvest Undead",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Necromancer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 10,
            "entries": [
                "You have learned more secrets about the nuances of life and death. Immediately after you become bloodied but not outright killed, you can take a Reaction to reduce an Undead creature under your control to 0 hit points. You then immediately regain a number of hit points equal to your Wizard level."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 14: Death's Master",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Necromancer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 14,
            "entries": [
                "Abstruse rituals within your spellbook allow you mastery over forces of death. While holding your spellbook you gain the following benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Bolster Undead",
                            "entries": [
                                "As a Bonus Action, an undead creature you have created or summoned within 60 feet of you gains temporary hit points equal to your Wizard level. A creature can gain these temporary hit points only once every 24 hours."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Burst Undead",
                            "entries": [
                                "When an undead creature under your control is reduced to 0 hit points, you can cause it to explode with necrotic energy. Roll a number of d6s equal to your Intelligence modifier and add them together. Each creature in a 10-foot emanation originating from the undead makes a Dexterity saving throw against your spell save DC. A target takes Necrotic damage equal to the number rolled on a failed save and half as much on a successful one."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Transmutation Savant",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Transmuter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Choose two Wizard spells from the Transmutation school, each of which must be no higher than level 1 or 2, and add them to your spellbook for free.",
                "In addition, whenever you gain access to a new level of spell slots in this class, you can add one Wizard spell from the Transmutation school to your spellbook for free. The chosen spell must be of a level for which you have spell slots."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Transmuter's Stone",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Transmuter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "When you finish a Long rest, you can create a magic stone that lasts until you use this feature again. A creature carrying the stone gains proficiency in Constitution saving throws and one of the following benefits chosen when you create the stone.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Darkvision",
                            "entries": [
                                "The bearer gains darkvision with a range of 60 feet or increases the range of its darkvision by 60 feet."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Resistance",
                            "entries": [
                                "The bearer gains resistance to Acid, Cold, Fire, Lightning, Poison or Thunder damage (you choose each time you choose this benefit)."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Speed",
                            "entries": [
                                "The bearer’s speed increases by 10 feet."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                "You can change the stone’s benefit when you cast a Transmutation spell using a spell slot."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Empowered Transmutation",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Transmuter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "When you cast a Transmutation spell using a spell slot, you can treat the spell as if it were cast using a spell slot 1 level above the slot expended. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long rest."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Potent Stone",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Transmuter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "Your Transmuter’s Stone is more versatile. When you create it, you can choose up to two benefits. You can choose each option other than Resistance only once, and if you choose Resistance twice, you must choose different damage types. You can change either or both benefits when you cast a Transmutation spell using a spell slot. In addition, the following are now among your benefit options for Transmuter’s Stone.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Evasive",
                            "entries": [
                                "The bearer can take the disengage action as a Bonus Action."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Tremorsense",
                            "entries": [
                                "The bearer gains Tremorsense with a range of 30 feet."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 10: Shapechanger",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Transmuter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 10,
            "entries": [
                "You always have the {@spell Polymorph|xphb} spell prepared and can cast it once without expending a spell slot. You regain the ability to cast it in this way when you finish a Long Rest. In addition, when you target yourself with the spell, you can modify the spell to gain the benefits below.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Game Statistics",
                            "entries": [
                                "You retain your personality, memories, and ability to speak. You also retain your Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma scores; class features; languages; and feats."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Transmute Spells",
                            "entries": [
                                "You can cast Transmutation spells while shapeshifted, except for any spell with a Material component that has a specified cost."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 14: Master Transmuter",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Transmuter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 14,
            "entries": [
                "While you carry your Transmuter’s Stone, you can take a Magic Action to consume the reserve of transmutation magic stored inside and choose one of the following benefits. After you use your Transmuter’s Stone in this way, the stone crumbles to dust. You can prevent the stone’s destruction by expending a level 5+ spell slot.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Major Transmutation",
                            "entries": [
                                "An object you touch— no larger than a 10-foot Cube or eight connected 5-foot Cubes —and transmute it into another nonmagical object of similar size and mass and of equal or lesser value."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Panacea",
                            "entries": [
                                "A creature you touch regains a number of Hit Points equal to half its Hit Point maximum (round down). Any curse affecting the target is lifted. If the target has the {@condition poisoned} or {@condition petrified} conditions, those conditions end."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Restore Life",
                            "entries": [
                                "You cast the {@spell Raise Dead|xphb} spell without expending a spell slot, using the stone in place of the required Material components."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Restore Youth",
                            "entries": [
                                "A willing creature you touch permanently appears {@dice 3d10} years younger, to a minimum of young adulthood."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Eyes of Night",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Cleric",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Twilight",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "As a Magic action, you touch a creature and bless it with eyes that see through the deepest gloom. For 1 hour, it gains Darkvision with a range of 120 feet and can see through magical darkness. Once you use this feature, you can't do so again until you finish a Long rest, unless you expend a spell slot of 2+ level to restore the use of it."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Twilight Sanctuary",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Cleric",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Twilight",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "As a Magic Action, you present your holy symbol and emanate a sphere of twilight. The sphere is a 30-foot radius emanation filled with dim light. It moves with you, and lasts for 1 minute or until you are {@condition incapacitated}. Whenever a creature ends its turn within the area, you can grant that creature temporary hit points equal to {@dice 1d6} + your Proficiency Bonus."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Improved Sanctuary",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Cleric",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Twilight",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "While your Twilight Sanctuary is active, you gain the following additional benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        "You gain Fly speed equal to your Speed.",
                        "Whenever a creature ends its turn within the area, you can choose to end one effect on it causing it to be {@condition charmed} or {@condition frightened}, instead of granting temporary hit points."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 17: Twilight Shroud",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Cleric",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Twilight",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 17,
            "entries": [
                "The twilight that you summon offers a protective embrace. You and your allies have half cover while in the emanation created by your Twilight Sanctuary."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Tool Proficiency",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Alchemist",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You gain proficiency with {@item alchemist's supplies|xphb} or another type of artisan's tools of your choice."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Experimental Elixir",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Alchemist",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You can prepare special vials to contain powerful potions called Experimental Elixirs. You can only have a number of vials up to your Intelligence modifier. When you finish a Long rest, you can fill your vials with elixirs rolling on the Experimental Elixir Table. At the start of your turn spend a spell slot and fill a number of vials equal to the spell slot level spent with Experimental Elixirs of your choice. A creature holding a vial can drink the elixir or administer it to a willing creature as a Bonus Action.",
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "colLabels": [
                        "1d6",
                        "Experimental Elixir Table"
                    ],
                    "colStyles": [
                        "col-1 text-center",
                        "col-11"
                    ],
                    "rows": [
                        [
                            "1",
                            "{@b Healing.} The drinker regains a number of hit points equal to {@dice 2d8} plus your Intelligence modifier. The number of Hit Points restored increases by {@dice 1d8} when you reach Artificer levels 9 ({@dice 3d8}) and 15 ({@dice 4d8})."
                        ],
                        [
                            "2",
                            "{@b Swiftness.} The drinker's Speed increases by 10 feet for 1 hour. This extra speed increases when you reach Artificer levels 9 (15 feet) and 15 (20 feet)."
                        ],
                        [
                            "3",
                            "{@b Resilience.} The drinker gains a +1 bonus to AC for 10 minutes. The duration increases when you reach Artificer levels 9 (1 hour) and 15 (8 hours)."
                        ],
                        [
                            "4",
                            "{@b Boldness.} The drinker can roll {@dice 1d4} and add the number rolled to every attack roll and saving throw they make for the next minute. The duration increases when you reach Artificer levels 9 (10 minutes) and 15 (1 hour)."
                        ],
                        [
                            "5",
                            "{@b Flight.} The drinker gains 15 feet of Fly Speed for 10 minutes. The Fly Speed increases when you reach Artificer levels 9 (20 feet) and 15 (30 feet)."
                        ],
                        [
                            "6",
                            "{@b Transformation.} The drinker gains the effect of {@spell Alter Self} for 10 minutes. The duration increases when you reach Artificer levels 9 (1 hour) and 15 (8 hours)."
                        ]
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 5: Alchemical Savant",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Alchemist",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 5,
            "entries": [
                "You're an expert in the use of chemicals to heal or harm. You gain the following benefits:",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Empowered Alchemy",
                            "entries": [
                                "You can add your Intelligence modifier to one roll of your Artificer spells that restore hit points or deal acid, fire or poison damage."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Chemical Toss",
                            "entries": [
                                "As a Bonus Action, make a spell attack against a creature within 30 feet of you. On a hit, the attack deals {@damage 2d6} + your Intelligence modifier acid damage."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 9: Restorative Reagents",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Alchemist",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 9,
            "entries": [
                "Your potions gain restorative properties. When a creature gains the effect of one of your Experimental Elixirs, it gains temporary hit points equal to {@dice 2d6} + your Intelligence modifier. Also, you can end one effect causing it to be {@condition Blinded}, {@condition Paralyzed}, or {@condition Poisoned}."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 15: Chemical Mastery",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Alchemist",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 15,
            "entries": [
                "Your neverending research on alchemy grants you the following benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Chemical Resistance",
                            "entries": [
                                "You gain Resistance to Acid damage and Poison damage. You also gain Immunity to the {@condition Poisoned} condition."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Conjured Cauldron",
                            "entries": [
                                "You can cast {@spell Tasha's Bubbling Cauldron} without expending a spell slot, without preparing the spell, and without Material components, provided you use Alchemist's Supplies as the Spellcasting Focus. Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a Long rest."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Tools of the Trade",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Armorer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You gain proficiency with heavy armor. You also gain proficiency with {@item smith's tools|xphb} or another type of artisan's tools of your choice."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Arcane Armor",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Armorer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "When you don a suit of armor you can transform it into your Arcane Armor. You gain the following benefits while wearing this armor.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        "You ignore the armor’s Strength requirement.",
                        "You can don or doff the armor as a {@action Utilize} action. The armor can't be removed against your will.",
                        "You can use the Arcane Armor as a Spellcasting Focus for your Artificer spells."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Armor Model",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Armorer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "When you don your arcane armor, choose one of the following armor models: Guardian or Infiltrator. The model you choose gives you special benefits while you wear it.",
                {
                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Guardian",
                    "entries": [
                        "{@b Thunder Gauntlets.} You can use Intelligence instead of Strength for the attack and damage rolls of your unarmed strikes. You can roll {@damage 1d8} in place of their normal damage and you can deal thunder or bludgeoning damage (your choice) when you deal damage with your unarmed strikes. Also, a creature you hit has disadvantage on attack rolls against targets other than you until the start of your next turn.",
                        "{@b Defensive Field.} As a bonus action, you can gain temporary hit points equal to your Artificer level. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Infiltrator",
                    "entries": [
                        "{@b Lightning Launcher.} A gemlike node appears on one of your armored fists or on the chest. It is a simple ranged weapon (range 100/300) that uses your Intelligence for attack and damage rolls. On a hit, it deals {@damage 2d6} lightning damage and applies the Vex mastery. Once every turn, on a hit you can deal {@damage 1d6} extra lightning damage.",
                        "{@b Powered Steps.} Your walking speed increases by 10 feet and you gain advantage on Dexterity ({@skill Stealth}) ability checks."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 5: Extra Attack",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Armorer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 5,
            "entries": [
                "You can attack twice, rather than once, whenever you take the {@action Attack} action."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 9: Armor Modifications",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Armorer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 9,
            "entries": [
                "Your Arcane Armor counts as separate items for the purposes of your Infuse Items feature: armor, boots, helmet and weapon. Each of those items can bear one of your infusions, and the infusions transfer over if you change your armor's model. Moreover, the number of items you can infuse increases by 2, but those extra items must be part of your Arcane Armor."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 15: Perfected Armor",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Armorer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 15,
            "entries": [
                "Your Arcane Armor gains additional benefits based on its model, as shown below.",
                {
                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Guardian",
                    "entries": [
                        "When a Huge or smaller creature you can see ends its turn within 30 feet of you, you can use your reaction to pull it up to 25 feet directly to an unoccupied space. If you pull the target to a space within 5 feet of you, you can make a melee weapon attack against it as part of this reaction."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Infiltrator",
                    "entries": [
                        "A creature hit by your Lightning Launcher has disadvantage on attack rolls against you. Also, the next attack roll against it has advantage, and deals {@damage 2d6} extra lightning damage on a hit."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Tools of the Trade",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Cartographer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You gain proficiency with {@item calligrapher's supplies|xphb} and {@item cartographer's tools|xphb}."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Adventurer's Atlas",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Cartographer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Whenever you finish a Long Rest, you can create a set of magical maps by touching a number of creatures equal to 1 plus your Intelligence modifier. Each target receives a magical map that lasts until you die or until you use this feature again. While carrying the map, a creature gains the following benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Awareness",
                            "entries": [
                                "The creature adds {@dice 1d4} to its Initiative rolls."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Positioning",
                            "entries": [
                                "The creature knows the location of all other map holders that are on the same plane of existence as itself. When casting a spell or creating an effect that requires seeing the target, a map holder can target another map holder regardless of sight or cover, so long as it is still within the effect's range."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Mapping Magic",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Cartographer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You gain the following benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Illuminated Cartography",
                            "entries": [
                                "You can cast {@spell Guiding Bolt} without expending a spell slot. You can do so a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long rest."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Portal Jump",
                            "entries": [
                                "On your turn, you can spend an amount of movement equal to half your Speed (round down) to teleport to an unoccupied space you can see within 15 feet of yourself or within 5 feet of a creature that is within 30 feet of you and holding one of your Adventurer's Atlas maps. You can't use this benefit if your Speed is 0."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 5: Guided Precision",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Cartographer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 5,
            "entries": [
                "Once per turn, whenever you deal damage with a spell from your Cartographer Spells list, you can add your Intelligence modifier to one damage roll of the spell."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 9: Ingenious Movement",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Cartographer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 9,
            "entries": [
                "When you use your Flash of Genius, you or a willing creature of your choice that you can see within 30 feet of yourself can teleport up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space you can see as part of that same Reaction."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 15: Superior Atlas",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Cartographer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 15,
            "entries": [
                "Your Adventurer's Atlas improves, gaining the following benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Safe Haven",
                            "entries": [
                                "When a map holder would be reduced to 0 hit points but not killed outright, that creature can destroy its map. The creature's hit points instead change to a number equal to twice your Artificer level, and the creature is teleported to an unoccupied space within 5 feet of you or another map holder of its choice."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Unerring Path",
                            "entries": [
                                "You can cast {@spell Find the Path} without expending a spell slot, without preparing the spell, and without needing spell components. Once you use this benefit, you can't use it again until you finish a Long Rest."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Tool Proficiency",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Forge Adept",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You gain proficiency with {@item smith's tools|xphb} or another type of artisan's tools of your choice."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Soul Weapon",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Forge Adept",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You learn to imbue a weapon with a fraction of your spirit. When you finish a Long Rest, you can touch a weapon and make it your Soul Weapon, thus gaining the following features.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        "You can use its Weapon Mastery property.",
                        "It gains a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls, unless it already grants a higher bonus. This bonus increases to +2 at Artificer level 9 and increases to +3 at level 14.",
                        "The weapon loses its attributes if you use this feature again."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Battle Ready",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Forge Adept",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Your combat training and your experiments with magic have paid off in two ways:",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        "You gain proficiency with martial weapons.",
                        "When you attack with a magic weapon, you can use your Intelligence modifier, instead of Strength or Dexterity modifier, for the attack and damage rolls."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 5: Extra Attack",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Forge Adept",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 5,
            "entries": [
                "You can attack twice, rather than once, whenever you take the {@action Attack} action."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 9: Runes of War",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Forge Adept",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 9,
            "entries": [
                "As a Bonus Action, you can create an aura in a 30-foot emanation that lasts for 10 minutes. The attacks of each ally in the emanation deal {@damage 1d4} extra Psychic damage. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of once) and you regain all expended uses after a Long rest."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 15: Perfect Weapon",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Forge Adept",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 15,
            "entries": [
                "When you take the {@action Attack} action, you can transfer some of your Soul Weapon’s bonus to your AC. For every 1 you reduce your attack and damage rolls by (maximum of 3), you gain +1 to your AC. This effect lasts until the start of your next turn. Also, when you finish a Long rest, you gain one of the following benefits until the end of your next long rest.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        "You have resistance to Psychic damage, and you can’t be {@condition charmed} or {@condition frightened}.",
                        "When you hit with your Soul Weapon the target takes {@damage 1d6} extra Psychic damage."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    "optionalfeature": [
        {
            "name": "Artificer Goggles",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "featureType": [
                "AI"
            ],
            "entries": [
                "{@i Prerequisite: a pair of goggles}",
                "These goggles have 4 charges. The wearer can expend 1 charge to cast the {@spell Darkvision} or {@spell Detect Magic} spell. The goggles regain {@dice 1d4} expended charges daily at dawn."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Bane Weapon",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "featureType": [
                "AI"
            ],
            "entries": [
                "{@i Prerequisites: Level 6+; A simple or martial weapon (requires attunement)}",
                "The weapon has 4 charges. This weapon grants a +1 bonus on attack and damage rolls made with it. When you infuse this item, choose one of these creature types: aberration, dragon, fiend or undead. When the wielder hits a creature of this type with the weapon, they can expend 1 charge to deal {@damage 2d6} extra force damage. The weapon's bonus increases to +2 when you reach Artificer level 10. The weapon regains {@dice 1d4} charges daily at dawn."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Blasting Focus",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "featureType": [
                "AI"
            ],
            "entries": [
                "{@i Prerequisite: Alchemist, Artillerist or Maverick subclasses (requires attunement)}",
                "This focus has 4 charges. Once every turn, when you cast an Artificer spell that deals cold, fire or lightning, you can expend 1 charge to gain one of the following benefits.",
                "One roll of the spell deals extra damage equal to your Artificer level.",
                "The spell ignores damage resistances.",
                "The focus regains {@dice 1d4} expended charges daily at dawn."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Bracer of Magical Strength",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "featureType": [
                "AI"
            ],
            "entries": [
